<CELL>3 0 0</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>Return of precept warrant, plat certificate and fiat</CELL>
<CELL>1 3 0</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>Governors and &s;ecretarys fees,</CELL>
<CELL>3 0 0</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>&nbsp;</CELL>
<CELL>&pound; 12 3 8 Str.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>&nbsp;</CELL>
<CELL>Equal to 52 Dollars.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>Him&s;elf, his &s;on, and negro eployed between November and April, in building a comfortable hou&s;e of &s;quare cypre&s;s timber, dove tailed, con&s;i&s;ting of two rooms and a loft, together with a corn-hou&s;e, and in clearing 8</CELL>
<CELL>&nbsp;</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>Carried forward</CELL>
<CELL>52&mdash;265D.</CELL>
</ROW>
<PB N="201" REF="014440_0220_0F92630A940073F0">
<ROW>
<CELL>brought over</CELL>
<CELL>52&mdash;265 D.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>acres of land, during which interval the maintenance of his family may be &s;uppo&s;ed to co&s;t</CELL>
<CELL>80 D.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>Allow that he buys in the &s;ame inter|val a cow,</CELL>
<CELL>12 D.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>2 &s;ows, 4 D.</CELL>
<CELL>8 D.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>a &s;tock of poultry,</CELL>
<CELL>6 D.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>&nbsp;</CELL>
<CELL>158 D.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>A hor&s;e</CELL>
<CELL>15 D.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>A canoe we may &s;uppo&s;e built by him&s;elf, iron work excepted,</CELL>
<CELL>2 D.</CELL>
